<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>chocolate soldier • toy soldier</xh5><p> <i>chocolate soldier</i>—(derog.) 1. a soldier unwilling to fight: They are <u>chocolate soldiers</u> who merely go to see battles and coolly urge others to fight them. 2. a militiaman or conscripted soldier: Conscripts, known as “chocos” (<u>chocolate soldiers</u>) were not required to serve outside prescribed areas.</p><p><i>toy soldier</i>—(also: tin soldier) 1. a miniature figure of a soldier made of metal, etc.: There are thousands of different hobbies: <u>toy soldiers</u>, model airplanes, cigarette cards. 2. <i>(derog.)</i> a soldier in a peacetime army; a ceremonial soldier only: Poor Hugo has gone clucking back for to be a <u>toy soldier</u> at Aldershot.</p> </entry>
